From 280ecb59b5f7ff334b8d9b1fa80c2167ae35f1c8 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Sat, 20 Jun 2026 03:30:48 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Replace Firebase with local Postgres + Dockerize backend

Implements roadmap items #9, #10, #1, #5, and #2:

- #9: All persistence moves from Firestore to a local PostgreSQL DB.
  The browser no longer talks to a database directly; it calls a new
  Express REST API (api.ts) backed by a pg connection pool (db.ts).
  Schema is created and seeded automatically on first boot.
- #10: Dockerfile (multi-stage) + docker-compose.yml bring up Postgres
  and the backend together. DB connection comes from DATABASE_URL.
- #1: Firebase removed entirely. The Gemini API key is no longer in
  source or a config file; it is stored in a settings table and entered
  via a new in-app Settings panel (write-only from the UI).
- #5: PORT is now an env var; removed the hardcoded footer email.
- #2: Notification IDs now come from the database, so read-state
  persists correctly across reloads.

Frontend mutation handlers were rewired to optimistic-update React
state and persist through the API; localStorage fallback removed.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
